Key Match Events: Brice Sensabaugh hit two 3-pointers and scored eight straight Utah points early in the fourth quarter, stretching an 11-point lead to 17.
Pre-Game Insights: Jazz picked up two victories in 24 hours in Florida, and they did it without most of their starting lineup.
Magic played without their top four scorers.
Post-Match Reflections: The Magic shot 36% overall and made 14 of 47 3-point shots (30%).
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz are 6-4 against Eastern Conference competition, and 3-21 against the West.
Seven of their nine wins have come on the road.
